  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0dad\u0ddc\u0dc3 \u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Lanka Sathosa offers the highest bid to bring canned fish",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Lanka Sathosa employees allege that Lanka Sathosa has given approval to a tender to buy 75,000 cans of fish at a higher price.",
        "The workers also say that while the local tinned fish producer's association had agreed to give a tin of fish weighing 425 grams to Sri Lanka Sathosa at a price of 620 rupees, the said company had rejected it and approved a tender to buy a tin of imported fish at a price of 700 rupees.",
        "They also point out that by getting 7500 imported tins at a higher price, Lanka Sathosa will lose nearly 60 lakh rupees."
      ],
